50|$|<b>Julian</b> day <b>number</b> is a {{count of}} days elapsed since Greenwich mean noon on 1 January 4713 B.C., Julian proleptic calendar. The Julian Date is the <b>Julian</b> day <b>number</b> {{followed}} by the fraction of the day elapsed since the preceding noon. Conveniently for astronomers, this avoids the date skip during an observation night.|$|R
