5000|$|The <b>Julian</b> Day <b>Number</b> (JDN) is the integer {{assigned}} to a whole solar day in the Julian day count starting from noon Universal time, with <b>Julian</b> day <b>number</b> 0 {{assigned to}} the day starting at noon on January 1, 4713 BC, proleptic Julian calendar (November 24, 4714 BC, in the proleptic Gregorian calendar), [...] a date at which three multi-year cycles started (which are: Indiction, Solar, and Lunar cycles) and which preceded any dates in recorded history. For example, the <b>Julian</b> day <b>number</b> for the day starting at 12:00 UT on January 1, 2000, was 2,451,545.|$|R
