5000|$|Such ordinal date formats {{are also}} used by many {{computer}} programs (especially those for mainframe systems). Using a three-digit <b>Julian</b> day <b>number</b> saves one byte of computer storage over a two-digit month plus two-digit day, for example, [...] "January 17" [...] is 017 in Julian versus 0117 in month-day format. OS/390 or its successor, z/OS, display dates in yy.ddd format for most operations.|$|R
